article.description: Jerri Taylor scored a season-high 18 points Tuesday night, leading Xavier to a 67-44 win over Kentucky.
article.headline: McGuff sets school record with 136th career win as Xavier tops Kentucky
article.linkText: Xavier's victory puts McGuff atop school's win list
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Jerri Taylor scored a season-high 18 points Tuesday night, leading Xavier (No. 21 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) to a 67-44 win over Kentucky that gave Kevin McGuff the career victory record for a Musketeers women's coach.

Xavier (6-2) has won six of its seven games against the Wildcats (4-2), who couldn't overcome cold starts to both halves.

McGuff improved to 136-61 in his seven seasons, moving one victory ahead of Melanie Balcomb's mark.

Kentucky went 11 minutes, 25 seconds without a field goal during a stretch of the first half, missing 15 consecutive shots while Xavier pulled ahead 36-11. The Wildcats opened the game in a 3-for-25 shooting funk with 11 turnovers.

Kentucky got the deficit down to 15 by halftime, but opened the second half in an 0-for-7 shooting slump with five turnovers, helping Xavier pull ahead by 30. Kentucky shot a season-low 21 percent from the field.
